cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.DS 

This paper is about improving deep neural networks by learning adaptive activation functions. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The experiments involve image classification, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper involves artificial intelligence techniques, which suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves optimization techniques, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
